Cinema Ticket Service

This project implements a ticket purchasing system for a cinema, adhering to the business rules and constraints provided in the problem description.

Key Features

Supports purchasing tickets of three types: Adult, Child, and Infant.
Ensures business rules such as:
A maximum of 25 tickets can be purchased at once.
Infant tickets are free but do not get allocated a seat.
Child and Infant tickets cannot be purchased without an accompanying Adult ticket.
Validates inputs, such as rejecting invalid account IDs and ensuring at least one Adult ticket is included when Child or Infant tickets are requested.
Communicates with external services to process payments and reserve seats.



